 :tx/rationale "C9-INSIGHT: The store must apply its own coherence machinery to its own knowledge — second-order epistemic closure. PROBLEM: The store has 134K datoms of accumulated knowledge including 226 audit observations from 4 independent agents. An agent sitting down to synthesize cannot use the store effectively — falls back to reading markdown files. The query interface supports first-order questions ('what observations exist?') but not second-order questions ('which findings converge across independent sources?', 'what is the dependency structure between findings?', 'what clusters emerge?'). The store has first-order knowledge (facts about the codebase) but not second-order knowledge (facts about the structure of its own fact-base). JUSTIFICATION: This is the observation-projection duality from SEED.md S6 applied reflexively. The store observes the codebase (first-order) but doesn't observe itself (second-order). The bilateral scan checks spec-impl alignment. Nothing checks knowledge-knowledge alignment — whether independent observations corroborate, contradict, or cluster. The concept engine clusters observations by semantic similarity — but only for domain observations, not for the store's own meta-observations. The seed assembles context — but uses keyword relevance, not convergence detection across independent sources. The machinery exists. It just isn't pointed at itself. From the Y-combinator insight (Session 038): if the system is a fixed-point combinator for knowledge, applying it to its own observation layer should be THE SAME OPERATION as applying it to external observations. The fact that it isn't is a meta-level C8 violation: the system treats its own knowledge differently from domain knowledge. Call this C9: the system must apply its own coherence machinery to its own knowledge, not just to the domain it manages. SOLUTION: When braid seed assembles context, run concept engine over recent observations, detect corroboration clusters (multiple independent sources = high certainty), detect contradictions, extract dependency structure from prose references, and surface the convergent findings as seed context. This is wiring, not invention — ~4h of connecting existing subsystems. VERIFICATION: braid seed --task 'determine next path forward' surfaces the top 5 convergent findings from the audit without the agent reading any markdown files. DEPENDENCIES: This should be done FIRST because it makes every subsequent session more effective. Every other task on the 264h roadmap will produce knowledge that needs synthesis. FILES: crates/braid-kernel/src/seed.rs, concept.rs, bilateral.rs. SEVERITY: Critical (meta-level). EFFORT: 4-8h."
